The Imo State Police Command has foiled an attempt by hoodlums to raze down Izombe Police Station in Oguta Local Government Area of the state. This is coming in less than 24 hours after hoodlums razed down Attah Police Station and Magistrate Court buildings in Njaba LGA of Imo State. The Commissioner of Police Imo State, CP Abutu Yaro disclosed this through a statement endorsed by the Police Public Relations Officer SP. Bala Elkana in Owerri on Sunday. The CP said that some hoodlums in their number launched an offensive on Izombe Police Station but were repelled by the gallant policemen on duty. According to the CP, four of the suspected arsonists were arrested during the attack while others escaped with bullet wounds. The CP commended the men for their abiding faith in the defence of the public space and urged them to be resilient in the fight until the enemies of the people were totally defeated. Yaro said that mop-up operation was ongoing with a view to arresting other fleeing members of the gang.  YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE Battle For First Bank: The Untold Story Last week was one of twists and turns for First Bank of Nigeria Limited, the nation’s oldest banking institution. It was a week that saw the bank’s MD sacked and reinstated, as major shareholders struggled for control of the financial powerhouse. SULAIMON OLANREWAJU reports… #EndSARS Panel: Drama As Witness Presents Video Evidence Of Slain Lekki Protesters A witness of the Lekki tollgate shooting incident, Miss Sarah Ibrahim has presented video evidence of people injured and killed at the scene to the Lagos State Judicial Panel. Tribune Online reports that… BUY OR SELL YOUR CAR IN 5 MINUTES WITH 2020CARS.NET CLICK HERE.  YOUR NEW CAR CONNECTS IN NIGERIA. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that
